{"post-91394": {"user": "Clan Yukimoto", "user_num": 2766, "timestamp": "1560804170000", "message": "The fires are always burning and the sound of metalworks fills the air. Here is where the great and masterful works of Tokhung are made. Minerals and metals taken from the mines and prisons of the Black Mountains are brought here, and while women work the billows to keep the fires hot and melt the metals into bars, the men work the forges to turn them into weapons, armor, and all manner of needs.If you come to this area, expect to find highly competitive prices between blacksmiths, as well as a culture for snobbery when comparing products. You may also get the distinct scent of sulfur and other chemicals heavy in your nose, with an underlying musk of sweat from the bodies that produce these goods.And if you are looking for work, you are sure to find it.", "link_list": [], "image_list": ["https://i.pinimg.com/564x/3d/78/8c/3d788caa13db98bac4148f3876180a84.jpg"], "html": "<div style=\"text-align:center;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://i.pinimg.com/564x/3d/78/8c/3d788caa13db98bac4148f3876180a84.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;\"/></div>"}}